hammer cleric of Tunare on the Brell Server, I was just wondering if any fellow clerics had, had any similar experiences to my own with this launch of an expansion.<br>
<br>
1.) Molments after logging on getting swarmed with tells from individuals which were in a group and were wiped out and all 6 need a resurrection.<br>
<br>
2.)  Out right RUDE responses when you deny your services.  I wish I could post a few of them, but Im sure I would get banned from this board.  <br>
<br>
3.)  Having people travel into DANGEROUS territory MINUS a cleric, screwing the pooch, getting wiped out, and having them bugg the be-jesus outa you to res them.  I know it seems that I rez the SAME people in the tower every night.  Well untill last night, when my ignore became 6 longer.<br>
<br>
Anyone else out there having these problems?  Just curious.<br>
<br>
Cinen NO REZ FOR YOU D00D Peacehammer<br>
50th circle of Tunare<br>
Brell  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukroscloudwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kros Cloudwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/17/01 12:56:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cityscope.net/~jackp/jack/kros.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ask me to Resurrect you?  Your Group? </span><hr size=1> You did not know that your are required by the Eula, to drop what you are doing anytime someone wants a rez and go rez them? <br>
<br>
I mean it says right there in the players manual that 'clerics are expected and required to give a rez any and all the request it. They must leave their group, drop what they are doing, and demand that the closest druid or wiz port them to the nearest port in order to expidite the rez'.<br>
<br>
OK, I am lying. It just seems some players think it is this way. I am always very greatful when a cleric takes the time out to give me a rez, even my guild clerics who often don't get shown the appreciation they should for doing it. I will admit I kinda expect a rez if I am on a dragon raid or the like, but I am still greatful for getting it. <p>Kros Cloudwalker,
Ranger of Karana,
Master Fletcher, Master Brewer,Council Elder of United Norrathian Brotherhood
<BR> <BR> Fazlazen Psychmaster, Enchanter of Prexus, Master Jeweler.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyshaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yshaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/17/01 4:27:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ask me to Resurrect you?  Your Group? </span><hr size=1> Try spending hours in Frenzy and having the same guy bring your corpse for a rez over and over.<br>
I said i would rez in frenzy room but would not leave, when i rez, the corpse has to be brought to me, ESPECIALLY in high population zones like guk and solb.<br>
Eventually i had the guy that i rezzed so many times pay, i only wanted 5pp but he payed nearly nine times that, good guy just a little death prone. <p>Yshaa Suppaheala
Dark Elf Cleric of 40 painful and erotic tortures.
Da Skurge
"Halfling...it does a body good"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarinonioakenshield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marinoni Oakenshield</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/18/01 9:50:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ask me to Resurrect you?  Your Group? </span><hr size=1> I have been spending a fair bit of time soloing the north wall of Karnors and I am consistantly getting tells to rez me or rez my party. Depending on mana or how nice they ask me I am usually more than willing to rez them. What gets me is that most of the time they do not donate anything for my time and mana for the rez, or if they do it is like 10pp. Then you see the same people offering 20-40pp for clarity or 30-40pp for a port. It bugs me that my rez, which saved them hours of hunting, and hours of getting loot is only worth nothing or almost nothing, but a spell that last only a few minutes or a port is so much more important. I am not saying everyone does, there are some people that donate quite well for my rez service, but the majority of the people think that because I am there, that I have to do it, it is my job to rez them. You may say that I am a greedy Cleric asking for donations, but I believe that a rez is one of the most important spells out there. It saves you a lot of time in lost experience, and can even restore a lost level, and I believe that it merits a lot more than a thanks or 10pp.<br>
<br>
Flame away.<br>
<br>
Marinoni Oakenshield<br>
51 Level Cleric of Brell<br>
The Combine Alliance<br>
